======================================================================
CHORD CO-PARTICIPATION THEOREM -- PROOF AND VERIFICATION
======================================================================

--- PART 1: THEOREM STATEMENT AND VERIFICATION ---

THEOREM: For Paley T_p at p = 3 mod 4, chord pair (a,b) with
min resonance q co-participates in 3-cycle gap triple iff:
  chi(q) = +1 AND chi(q+1) = -1, OR
  chi(q) = -1 AND chi(q-1) = +1

  p=7: 3/3 correct, 0 wrong
  p=11: 10/10 correct, 0 wrong
  p=19: 36/36 correct, 0 wrong
  p=23: 55/55 correct, 0 wrong
  p=31: 105/105 correct, 0 wrong
  p=43: 210/210 correct, 0 wrong


--- PART 2: ALGEBRAIC PROOF ---

For qa = b (positive resonance), a in QR:
  qr(a) = a, chi(qa) = chi(q)*chi(a) = chi(q)
  If chi(q)=+1: qr(b) = qa, g3 = p - a - qa = p - a(1+q)
    chi(g3) = chi(-a(1+q)) = chi(-1)*chi(a)*chi(1+q)
           = (-1)(+1)*chi(1+q) = -chi(1+q)
  If chi(q)=-1: qr(b) = p-qa, g3 = p - a - (p-qa) = qa - a = a(q-1)
    chi(g3) = chi(a)*chi(q-1) = (+1)*chi(q-1) = chi(q-1)

For qa = b, a in QNR:
  qr(a) = p-a, chi(qa) = chi(q)*chi(a) = chi(q)*(-1)
  If chi(q)=+1: chi(qa)=-1, qr(b) = p-qa
    g3 = p - (p-a) - (p-qa) = a + qa - p = a(1+q) - p
    chi(g3) = chi(a(1+q)) = chi(a)*chi(1+q) = (-1)*chi(1+q) = -chi(1+q)
  If chi(q)=-1: chi(qa)=+1, qr(b) = qa
    g3 = p - (p-a) - qa = a - qa = a(1-q)
    chi(g3) = chi(a)*chi(1-q) = (-1)*chi(-(q-1)) = (-1)*chi(-1)*chi(q-1)
           = (-1)*(-1)*chi(q-1) = chi(q-1)

CONCLUSION: chi(g3) depends ONLY on q, not on a:
  chi(q)=+1 => chi(g3) = -chi(q+1)
  chi(q)=-1 => chi(g3) = chi(q-1)

Copart > 0 iff chi(g3) = +1, so:
  chi(q)=+1: copart iff chi(q+1) = -1
  chi(q)=-1: copart iff chi(q-1) = +1

QED.


